[30;1m100 | [0m[35m//! A list is a doubly linked list. That is, it is a Sequence that supports both[0m
[30;1m101 | [0m[35m//! forward and backward traversal, and (amortized) constant time insertion and[0m
[30;1m102 | [0m[35m//! removal of elements at the beginning or the end, or in the middle. Lists have[0m
[30;1m103 | [0m[35m//! the important property that insertion and splicing do not invalidate iterators[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m706[0m[34m of [0m[33m1464[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/ray/cpp/example/thirdparty/include/boost/container/slist.hpp[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m126 | [0m[35m//! result in disastrously slow programs. The problem is that insert's first argument is[0m
[30;1m127 | [0m[35m//! an iterator p, and that it inserts the new element(s) before p. This means that[0m
[30;1m128 | [0m[35m//! insert must find the iterator just before p; this is a constant-time operation[0m
[30;1m129 | [0m[35m//! for list, since list has bidirectional iterators, but for slist it must find that[0m
[30;1m130 | [0m[35m//! iterator by traversing the list from the beginning up to p. In other words:[0m
[30;1m131 | [0m[35m//! insert and erase are slow operations anywhere but near the beginning of the slist.[0m
[30;1m132 | [0m[35m//![0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m707[0m[34m of [0m[33m1464[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m125 | [0m[35m//! functions insert and erase. Using these member functions carelessly, however, can[0m

[30;1m128 | [0m[35m//! insert must find the iterator just before p; this is a constant-time operation[0m
[30;1m129 | [0m[35m//! for list, since list has bidirectional iterators, but for slist it must find that[0m

[30;1m107 | [0m[35m//! element, but not to the previous element. That is, it is a Sequence that[0m

[30;1m106 | [0m[35m//! An slist is a singly linked list: a list where each element is linked to the next[0m
[30;1m107 | [0m[35m//! element, but not to the previous element. That is, it is a Sequence that[0m
[30;1m108 | [0m[35m//! supports forward but not backward traversal, and (amortized) constant time[0m
[30;1m109 | [0m[35m//! insertion and removal of elements. Slists, like lists, have the important[0m
[30;1m110 | [0m[35m//! property that insertion and splicing do not invalidate iterators to list elements,[0m
[30;1m111 | [0m[35m//! and that even removal invalidates only the iterators that point to the elements[0m
[30;1m112 | [0m[35m//! that are removed. The ordering of iterators may be changed (that is,[0m

[30;1m100 | [0m[35m//! A list is a doubly linked list. That is, it is a Sequence that supports both[0m
[30;1m101 | [0m[35m//! forward and backward traversal, and (amortized) constant time insertion and[0m
[30;1m102 | [0m[35m//! removal of elements at the beginning or the end, or in the middle. Lists have[0m
